cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.PL, cs.ETM 

The paper deals with the distributed power control problem in microgrids, which involves the coordination of multiple agents. This falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also addresses communication delays and imperfect communication, which are common issues in distributed systems and networks, making cs.DC another likely sub-category. The use of real-time implementation and power loss considerations suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of computer engineering (cs.CE) and power systems (cs.PL). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for solving the power control problem, which involves mathematical optimization and iterative methods, making the sub-category of emerging technologies (cs.ETM) a possible fit as well.
